.TH add_ndr  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBadd_ndr\fR \-  Adds a non-default rule for objects. You can also remove vias from the NDR
.SH Syntax      \fBadd_ndr\fR    [-help]    [-add_via {<via_name1 via_name2
...>}]  [-exclude_backside_via]  [-generate_via]    [-hard_spacing]    [-init <string>]    [-min_cut {layer1[:layer2] <min_cut
...>}]    [-spacing <string> | -spacing_multiplier <string>]    [-via {<via_name1 via_name2
...>}]    [-width <string> | -width_multiplier <string>]    {-name <ruleName>}  [-use_via_cut_class <string>] 
.P Adds a non-default rule for objects. You can also remove vias from the NDR. The command checks the generateVias mode and if setGenerateViaMode is set to -auto true, the generated vias is used irrespective of the -generate_via option. You can use the command at any point in the design flow. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each   add_ndr parameter. For a detailed description of the command and all   of its parameters, use the man command: man add_ndr  "\fB-add_via {<via_name1 via_name2
...>}\fR" Adds vias to the existing via list. You can use this parameter to add DFM vias or other custom vias.  "\fB-exclude_backside_via\fR" Prevents inclusion of non-route or backside vias in a newly defined non-default rule.   "\fB-generate_via\fR" Auto-generates vias with the generateVia command.  Note: If the NDR specified by you is with metal wider than the default rule,   it is recommended to use this option for getting better routing results.  "\fB-hard_spacing\fR" Sets the non-default rule as HARDSPACING.   "\fB-init <string>\fR" Specifies the name of an existing non-default rule from which all values are initialized.  Note:  Other options will over-write these values.  "\fB-min_cut {layer1[:layer2] <min_cut
...>}\fR" Specifies the minimum cut limit for via layers.  "\fB-name <ruleName>\fR" Specifies the name of the non-default rule that is to be added.   "\fB-spacing {layer1[:layer2] <spacing
...>}\fR" Specifies the spacing for routing layers.  "\fB-spacing_multiplier {layer1[:layer2] <spacing_multiplier>}\fR" Spacing multiplier for routing layers.  "\fB-use_via_cut_class <string>\fR" Specifies multiple layer definition and cut_class list to support the LEF/DEF property. The value must be given in the format of either  {layer cut_class} or  {layer cut_class nr_row nr_col}. Refer to the examples below:   add_ndr -name new_1 -use_via_cut_class {V1 VX}  add_ndr -name new_2 -use_via_cut_class {V1 VX 2 1}   add_ndr -use_via_cut_class {{V1 VX 2 1} {V2 VH 2 1}
.....}   "\fB-via {<via_name1 via_name2
...>}\fR" Resets and adds the list of via or via rule generate name.  "\fB-width {layer1[:layer2] <width
...>}\fR" Specifies the width for routing layers.  "\fB-width_multiplier {layer1[:layer2] <width_multiplier
...>}\fR" Width multiplier for routing layers. 
.SH Examples
.RS  "*" 2 The following command creates a rule that requires extra spacing. All other values are the same as the default rule.  add_ndr -name default_2x_space -spacing {metal1:metal4 0.2 metal5:metal6 0.4 metal7 0.6}  "*" 2 The following command creates a new wide-wire routing rule (double wide on the Mx routing layers, but not the wide layers).   Auto-generate vias because the width changed, so the default vias are not correct.  add_ndr -name Mx_2x_wide -width {metal1:metal4 0.20} -generate_via  "*" 2 The following command uses existing wide-wire rule, but require 2 cut vias for the Vx layers (via1 to via3)  add_ndr -name Mx_2x_wide_Vx_2cut -init Mx_2x_wide -min_cut {via1:via3 2}
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 modify_ndr  "*" 2 exportNdr  "*" 2 setGenerateViaMode  "*" 2 generateVias  "*" 2 Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide
.RE
.P
